{"word":"G2116 - εὐθύνω - euthýnō - yoo-thoo'-no - Governor","sections":[{"paragraph":"<strong>மூல வார்த்தை / Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">εὐθύνω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>எழுத்துமாற்றம் / Transliteration: </strong><span class=\"transliteration\">euthýnō</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>ஒலிபெயர்ப்பு / Phonetic: </strong><span class=\"phonetic\">yoo-thoo'-no</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>சுருக்க விளக்கம் / Short Definition: </strong><span class=\"short-definition\">Governor</span>"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"parts-of-speech\"><strong>இலக்கண சொல்வகை / Part(s) of speech: </strong>Adverb / வினையடை</span>"},{"paragraph":"செவ்வை பண்ணு, திருப்பு - வினையடை"},{"paragraph":"1. to make straight, level, plain"},{"paragraph":"2. to lead or guide straight, to keep straight, to direct"},{"paragraph":"<span class=\"original-in-english\"><strong>ஆங்கில மூலம் / Original in English: </strong>From <a href=\"#/G2117 - εὐθύς - euthýs - yoo-thoos'/2117\">G2117</a>; to <i>straighten</i> (<i>level</i>); technically to <i>steer:</i> - governor, make straight.</span>"},{"paragraph":""}]}